.TH "getIndex" "1" "" "SequoiaDB User Manuals" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
getIndex \- get the specified index
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]db.collectionspace.collection.getIndex(<name>)\f[]
.SH CATEGORY
.PP
Collection
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Get the specified index from current collection.
.SH PARAMETERS
.IP \[bu] 2
name ( \f[I]String\f[], \f[I]Required\f[] )
.PP
Name of the specified index.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note\f[]
.IP \[bu] 2
Index name should not contain null string, "." or "$".
The length of it should not be greater than 127B.
.RE
.SH RETURN VALUE
.PP
When the function executes successfully, it will return a specified index whose
type is BSONObj.
.PP
When the function fails, an exception will be thrown and an error message will
be printed.
.SH ERRORS
.PP
